        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000" >
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:400; margin-top:2px;">Pope Leo’s challenges with Africa</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/pope-leo-xiv-sworn-in-modern-challenges-church.png" alt="Pope Leo XIV, was sworn in earlier this month and is now tasked with guiding the Church through increasingly modern challenges" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
         <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>
          Pope Leo XIV, was sworn in earlier this month and is now tasked with guiding the Church through increasingly modern challenges. Credits: Guglielmo Mangiapane, Reuters
          </i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         Pope Leo XIV’s rise comes at a crucial time for the Catholic Church in Africa. The <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-may-25-analysis-h1-1-faith-is-growing?source=-website" target="_blank">faith is growing</a> rapidly, but faces considerable challenges. After Pope Francis’s deep engagement with Africa, many hoped the next pope would be from Africa. Consequently, Pope Leo has high expectations to support African issues like poverty, political instability, and climate change.
            </p>
            <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          A key issue is the regional shortage of priests, which mirrors a global trend. This threatens the Church’s growth and care for its followers. The Catholic Church is also in competition with Pentecostal churches, which attract many Africans with promises of quick solutions to their struggles. Pentecostal denominations and leaders dictate the public happenings in Ghana, Nigeria, South Africa, Zambia, and Zimbabwe.
            </p>
            <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Pope Leo must make the Catholic Church relevant while maintaining its doctrine. He must also address rising debates over LGBTQ+ rights, which many Catholics in Africa oppose. Prominent African clerics, such as Cardinal Fridolin Ambongo of the DRC, have endorsed him, urging unity and prayer. 
            </p>
            <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Currently, countries across the Sahel and other parts of the continent are under the sway of Islamist extremism perpetrated by various Jihadist groups. Africa has an estimated 281Mn or 20% of the Catholic Church followers. 
            </p>
          </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
