        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-may-25-ktt-h1-5-chile?source=-website" target="_blank">Chile</a> is a South American country with a long, narrow shape along the Pacific coast. It experiences various climates, from the coastal desert beginning in the tropical north to the cold subantarctic southern tip. Chile has a stable economy, mainly due to copper exports. It is one of the only countries in Latin America that has a visa waiver to the US, and it is also granted visa-free entry to the EU, China, and Russia.
            </p>
            <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         Chile has a strong democratic tradition. However, it wasn’t always the case. It faced a military dictatorship under Pinochet from 1973 to 1990. Recently, Chile has seen significant political changes. There is a movement for constitutional reform aiming to tackle issues like inequality, indigenous rights, and social justice in the post-dictatorship era.
            </p>
          </mj-text>
